  <front>
   <head>The ANSWER.</head>
  </front>
  <body>
   <lg xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" type="poem">
    <lg n="1" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="1" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">WHEN I, in feeble Verse, essay'd</l>
     <l n="2" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">NASSAU and ANNA's Praise,</l>
     <l n="3" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">A Lyric Muse flew o'er my Head,</l>
     <l n="4" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And dropp'd a Branch of Bays:</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="2" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="5" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">I would have fix'd it on my Brow;</l>
     <l n="6" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">But PHOEBUS said, Forbear;</l>
     <l n="7" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">'Tis  to  the Bough,</l>
     <l n="8" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">And  to</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="3" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="9" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Give it the Bard, who boldly dares</l>
     <l n="10" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Attempt the  Lyre;</l>
     <l n="11" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Who wisely checks, but not impairs</l>
     <l n="12" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The tow'ring PINDAR's Fire.</l>
    </lg>
    <lg n="4" stanza_type="quatrain">
     <l n="13" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">Thus, Sir, to you, in PHOEBUS' Name,</l>
     <l n="14" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">The Laurel Wreath I send;</l>
     <l n="15" met="-+|-+|-+|-+" line_length="8">And, since the God denies  Fame,</l>
     <l n="16" met="-+|-+|-+" line_length="6">Am glad it crowns my</l>
    </lg>
   </lg>
  </body>
